            <p>Heart Machine, the studio behind sci-fi Zelda-like Hyper Light Drifter, has a new metroidvania out next month called Possessor(s).</p>
<p>Publisher Devolver released a new gameplay overview trailer over the weekend revealing its PS5 and PC release date of 11th November.</p>
<p>Possessor(s) is a metroidvania (or "search action" game, as the developers are describing it) set in a quarantined cyberpunk city, with players taking the role of high school student Luca who's struck a deal with a demon.</p>

